Constants: get_session_keys, get_traffic_items, get_traffic_ce, get_traffic_hls, get_traffic_headers, get_traffic_application_profiles

Description: Specifies a list of port handles. If this parameter exists, only the keys related to the given ports are returned.

Specifies which traffic elements should be used. Is a list. For modes get_traffic_ce/get_traffic_hls this needs to be a traffic item name (stream id). Because this parameter is a list, the traffic item names should be properly formatted (in case of containing spaces). For mode get_traffic_headers this needs to be a configElement/highLevelStream IxNetwork handle.

May contains a list of value that specify an inclusion filter for the returned session keys. The keys that have items in <typepath> are dependent on the command that generated that kind of typepath. Generally the procedure that generated those objects has the same name as the first part in the key.
Eg.: in emulation_bgp_route_config.bgp_sites.<vport/protocols/bgp/neighborRange/l2Site> objects of type vport/protocols/bgp/neighborRange/l2Site are generated by the emulation_bgp_route_config command.
